Package com.purnendu.quizo.dao

Interface AdminDao

public interface AdminDao
This interface handles the data access object (DAO) for admin-related operations, specifically for managing Admin entities. It leverages Room Persistence Library annotations such as Dao, Insert, Update, Query, and uses standard Java collections like List.
Version:
2.0.1
Author:
Purnendu Guha

  • Method Details

    • insertAdmin

      void insertAdmin(Admin admin)
      Inserts a new Admin into the database. If an admin with the same primary key (email) already exists, a conflict strategy (e.g., REPLACE, IGNORE) should be defined in the annotation if needed, otherwise, a SQLiteConstraintException will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      admin - The Admin object to insert.

    • updateAdmin

      void updateAdmin(Admin admin)
      Updates an existing Admin record in the database. The update is based on the primary key (email) of the provided Admin object.
      Parameters:
      admin - The Admin object to update.

    • observeAllAdmins

      List<Admin> observeAllAdmins()
      Retrieves all Admin records from the 'admin' table. This query returns a list of all administrators currently stored in the database.
      Returns:
      A List of Admin objects.
